<div type="definition">
<p>CONTROL CRUELLY.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The most common general word for oppression is probably nè 虐 (ant. cí 慈 "show loving care for").</p>
<p>2. Bào 暴 (ant. fǔ 撫 "care well for") emphasises the aspect of violence.</p>
<p>3. Líng 陵 (ant. yù 育 "take loving care of", and the rare jí 藉, and chéng 乘 emphasise the abuse of supremacy of social or political position.</p>
        </div>
